methods.clearScriptPathLoader: Removes the currently configured script path loader from this script.
methods.dropReference: Drop a previously-retained reference to this referent.
methods.evaluateScript:
Evaluates the script and manages liveness of objects that are exported to the user. This method should be called
 from the serial executor as it manipulates static state.

*Overload 1*  
  :param script: (java.lang.String) - the code to execute
  :param scriptName: (java.lang.String) - an optional script name, which may be ignored by the implementation, or used improve error
          messages or for other internal purposes
  :return: (io.deephaven.db.util.ScriptSession.Changes) the changes made to the exportable objects
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param scriptPath: (java.nio.file.Path) - the path to the script to execute
  :return: (io.deephaven.db.util.ScriptSession.Changes) the changes made to the exportable objects
methods.getVariable:

Retrieve a variable from the script session's bindings.
 
 Please use ScriptSession.getVariable(String, Object) if you expect the variable may not exist.

  :return: (java.lang.Object) the variable

If this referent is "live", behave as LivenessReferent.retainReference() and return true. Otherwise, returns false rather
 than throwing an exception.

:return: (boolean) True if this referent was retained, false otherwise

text:
The delegating script session delegates all calls to another script session. When evaluating a script it massages the
 Changes to the QueryScope so that any modifications that are being seen for the first time by the api-client come
 across as new entries and not as modified entries.
